<%# Two-section keybindings reference card. "local" page actions
    render FIRST (above the hairline) so the user sees context-
    specific affordances at the top; the always-true "global"
    navigation surface follows below. The "local" section + hairline
    are both OMITTED when `local_groups` is empty — see the component
    class for the deny-list + default-fallback rules.

    Renamed 2026-05-18 — "page actions" → "local", "navigation" →
    "global". The "global" surface was also trimmed to /games +
    /settings + logout only.

    Group layout — `local_groups` and `global_groups` return Group
    structs (`{ layout:, items: }`). A group with `layout: :grid_2col`
    renders inside `<div class="keybindings-grid keybindings-grid--two-col">`
    with an inline `grid-template-rows: repeat(half, auto)` so items
    fill COLUMN-FIRST (5 left / 3 right for an 8-item group, 1 left /
    1 right for a 2-item group). A single-column group renders rows
    in the default `display: block` flow. Visible hairlines render
    BETWEEN groups (never at the very top or bottom) regardless of
    which layout each group uses. %>
<div class="keybindings-reference">
  <% if local_groups.any? %>
    <section class="keybindings-section keybindings-page-actions" data-section="local">
      <h3><%= t("keybindings.sections.local") %></h3>
      <%= render_groups(local_groups) %>
    </section>
    <hr class="hairline">
  <% end %>

  <section class="keybindings-section keybindings-navigation" data-section="global">
    <h3><%= t("keybindings.sections.global") %></h3>
    <%= render_groups(global_groups) %>
  </section>
</div>
